inn1.comm: starts off with a full and wide one outside off but not wide enough to be called, left alone
that's a low full toss which he fails to put away, tamely pushed to mid-off
that's a nice on-the-target delivery, skids towards the off stump and Strauss pats it back
fullish on the off stump and dug out back towards the bowler
lands it on a good length outside off, not much away movement before reaching the keeper
false shot from Strauss, he shapes to play a back-foot punch but the extra bounce beats and ultimately saves him
hits it outside off and Denly safely sees it through to the keeper
now Denly's sucked into the drive, this time on the front foot, Bracken angles it nicely across him
takes a couple of steps down the pitch and Bracken fires it on the blockhole, Denly does well too dig it out
shuffles across and clips it straight to short square leg
stays beside the line and steers it towards point
he waltzes down the track again to biff that out of the ground but ends up swishing at thin air, this time Bracken drops it much shorter, another maiden
pushes it towards mid-off and he's cruelly denied a run, something's got to give
cheers as Strauss pulls that between mid-on and square leg, Ferguson gives a good chase and relays it to Hauritz close to the rope
pushes it straight back to the bowler
excellent delivery, gets it to kick up off a good length and fizz past Strauss who drops his hand
stays beside the line and taps it away to the off side
a little slower in pace and Strauss shapes to angle it past the gap square on the off side
looked like the off cutter which forced Denly to change his mind on the shot, he plays it with soft hands to the off side
angled on middle and leg and whipped to short square leg
outside off and pushed straight back to Bracken
just strays on the pads and Denly works it on its way to fine leg, more cheers from the crowd
nicely punched off the backfoot and Clarke doesn't have to move an inch at backward point to stop that
tries to mow it across the line but he only just manages to beat mid-on
this one is shorter and stops on him a bit, in the air for a second or two but safe from the bowler
that's a nice shot, a tad short of a length outside off and a fraction of width, he stands tall and punches it past the gap between backward point and cover
Watson gets in the way of a booming off drive at mid-off, well done Shane
that's a gift, on the pads and the half volley is easily worked away past square leg and fine leg is too fine to cut it off
forget about chasing that, another half volley on the pads and he tucks it squarer this time, past the gap between short square leg and mid-on
mixes it up with a slower one, he doesn't pick it right and the outside edge drops short of second slip
strays on the pads and he works it to fine leg
after the rehearsals in the previous over Denly shows exactly how it's done, he waltzes down the track, picks the slower ball and lofts it well clear of mid-on
that's shorter in length and there's a thick outside edge which safely clears the slips
that would have been a stunner from Clarke at backward point, leaps to his right with both hands cupped, Strauss slashes outside off and takes the aerial route, that went like lightning
pushes a full delivery to the off side
keeps it along the ground past backward point and gets the desired result, stays beside the line and times the cut well
this one keeps a bit low outside off and passes underneath his bat
stays back and pushes it to the off side
comes back in a bit off the seam and Denly almost edges it onto his pads
slower and fuller, pushes it to mid-on
hope someone took a snap of that, good length on middle and off and Denly stays at the crease, picks the length early and whips it in the air over midwicket, that's a shot Gibbs will be proud of
he oversteps and denly works it back to the bowler
Free Hit all it costs is a single to mid-off, Siddle gets away with a full delivery
punches it towards the covers and takes a single
works his wrists and turns it into the wide spaces at midwicket to pick up anj easy single
Denly had his heart in his mouth as he chipped it in the air towards mid-on, luckily the fielder was deep
shows the full face of the bat and pushes it to the off side
and that's followed by a false shot, Johnson changes his pace and teases Denly into chasing that outside off
bowls it straight on the off stump line and he pushes it back to the bowler, nice opening over
keeps it on a good length outside off and he makes use of the width to steer it to third man
full on the leg stump but he fails to beat short fine leg
that's a nice yorker length delivery, he digs it out and the ball rolls to the on side
fullish and tucked to the on side for a single
stands tall and punches it hard but can't beat cover
he'll be kicking himself for not putting away a friendly full toss, tamely tucks it to mid-on
fast inswinging yorker on the leg stump, he takes it on the full but places it straight to fine leg
opts for the shorter length and forces Denly on the backfoot, tapped to the off side

well for a split second I thought he dragged it onto his stumps! Lands on the blockhole outside off and Denly gets on his knee and shapes to play a square drive, the inside edge thuds onto his boot and stops in front of the stumps
tapped to the off side
that's a mid-afternoon thrash by Denly, short of a length on the off stump and he makes a bit of room and cracks it past mid-off and cover
opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man, they take on the second run and Strauss is struggling for a bit but he makes his ground
slower ball and Strauss swings too early, the ball loops towards the keeper
slower in pace, he works it towards square leg
good length outside off and he steers it to third man
gets forward and just manages to squeeze it past a diving backward point, not sure who the fielder was
chops it straight to Clarke at backward point
slower ball lands outside leg and Strauss gets a leading edge to the off side
goes right across his stumps and works it to fine leg, cheers for England's 50
bowls it wide outside off and much to his horror it doesn't spin
gets across and works it to the on side
gets forward, the ball clips the top flap of his pad and lobs to slip
stays back and punches it along the ground to long-on
chips down the ground and Hauritz fires that on the leg stump, he forces it to mid-on and challenges the fielder
spins a bit, he punches it off the backfoot to cover
drops it short and Strauss shapes to pull it away but he checks his shot and the ball rolls past square leg
comes down the pitch and gives a bit of room, chips it in the air but the ball drops short of point
full on the pads and clipped away straight to deep square leg
keeps it a bit short and Strauss fails to pierce the off side field
that slower short delivery again, Strauss doesn't pick it all that well and pulls too early, he manages to keep it along the ground though
plays a checked-drive to mid-off
lovely shot, he chips down the track on seeing the flight and plays the cleanest of lofts over the bowler's head

the reverse sweep costs him his wicket, he's onto the shot too early and the ball doesn't spin too much and clips him low on the front pad, after a fairly prolonged appeal Asad Rauf is convinced, that had to have hit just the off stump, I'd like to see another replay of that. I think I saw an under edge, not the cleanest of dismissals
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
overthrows! They push a quick single to mid-on and Johnson fires it to Paine but the throw is too wide and even the fielder backing up failed to cut it off
pushed back to the bowler
full outside off and pushed past the covers
drops it short outside off and he chops it down to third man
drops it shorter in length and he defends back to the bowler
stays at the crease and pushes it to the off side
hits the deck hard and the ball climbs on Bopara but he easily manages to clip it to the on side

he can describe this shot to his grand kids some day! Full in length on the off stump and he shows a dead straight bat and scoops it so easily over the bowler's head, the head position and follow through looked perfect, too bad the ball just dropped short of the rope
full outside off and driven to the off side
flighted on middle and leg and clipped to the on side
moves about at his crease and tries to ciut but he mistimes it back to the bowler
full on the off stump and clipped to the on side
drops it a bit short on seeing him advance, the ball lobs off his pads and rolls away
one of the uglier boundaries this afternoon, he chases a wide delivery and the under edge beats the keeper and races to third man
reaches out to chase another wide delivery and he takes a sharp single to cover point
chases a wide one again and the ball beats him
drops it short of a length down the leg side and Bopara shuffles a bit and whips it in the air well wide of short fine leg
checks his cover drive but the ball still races away, Bopara challenges Hauritz's throw from the deep and makes his ground

chance for Australia! Bopara drops his wrists and takes a cheeky single, poor Denly has a lot of ground to cover with a rampaging Johnson running beside him, the bowler's under-arm flick just misses the stumps with a diving Denly a few inches short of his crease
slower ball and he shuffles and clips it down to fine leg
stays beside the line and thumps it to the off side
swishes hard outside the off stump and the ball creeps underneath the bat
pushes it softly back to the bowler
stays behind the line and taps it back to the bowler
the first wicket-taking delivery he has bowled, the jaffa squares him up outside off, extra bounce and Bopara gets his glove out of the way
comes round the wicket with the keeper upto the stumps, the batsman works it to the on side
that's a street slog from Denly which fetches him nothing, he makes room and the ball somehow dodges the outside edge and the stumps
makes room and works it back to the bowler
mistimed straight drive by Denly and Bracken does superbly to fling himself to his right and save a few runs
clips it with the angle behind square on the on side
makes room and cracks it past the gap at cover
strolls down the pitch for another free whack but Watson drops it shorter and the ball once again misses the top of the stumps
attempts the pull again but plays it along the ground

goes for the home run, gets a lot of elevation but not the desired distance, Bopara gets his front pad across and lofts across the line, Hauritz is there at deep square leg and he takes it comfortably
gets beside the line and pushes it to the off side
gets forward and steers it past the big gap between mid-off and cover
plays a checked drive to long-on, Bracken continues round the wicket
slower delivery angling on middle and leg, he defends back to the bowler
another slower one, outside off and he steers it to the off side, Denly charges out of his crease and heads back quickly
opens the face and squeezes a single to the covers
pushes it with soft hands towards mid-off
stays beside the line and he opens the face and steers it towards third man
fires it flatter and quicker, he whips it to deep square leg
flat and short again, he clips it to the on side
chips down the track and checks his shot, pushes it back to the bowler
uses his feet at the crease and cuts it to the off side
comes down the track and checks his loft, the ball drops well short of long-on
shapes to slice it away through the off side, the extra turn foxes him and he chops it away

several shouts of 'catch it' from where I'm sitting but nothing from the Australians, he chips a full delivery in the air towards mid-off, seemed dangerous but his placement was actually quite perfect
pushes it to the off side to the left of cover

that's another give-away I'm afraid, Johnson angles it across the right-hander from round the wicket and Denly shuffles right across and whips it high in the air over the on side, catching practice for Hussey running forward from deep square leg
stays beside the line and works it to the off side
nice sharp bouncer, hits the deck hard and Prior just manages to keep away from it as it fizzes past his body
very watchful there, he just allows that to go through to the keeper, no turn
chipped drive towards mid-on, young Paine got a little excited there
attempts to cut him through the off side, but the ball beats him
goes on the backfoot and cuts through point
pushed straight back to the bowler
full on middle and leg and drives neatly to long-on

that just flew off the bat, makes use of the width outside off, didn't cut it with much conviction because the ball was in the air for a bit, but the placement was spot on because third man had no chance
stays back and pushes it back to the bowler
pushed down the track again
Johnson drops it short outside off and the ball stops on him a bit, Shah meets the ball high on the bat and slaps it past midwicket and mid-on, Johnson knows he's bowled a poor one
opens the face of the bat and steers him to third man
stays beside the line and taps it towards point and takes a quick single
Hauritz gives him width and pays, Prior slashes hard and gets a thickish outside edge which just beats the diving short third man
gets on his knee, fetches it from outside off and sweeps it in the air towards deep square leg, ferguson fumbles
flat and quick, he shapes to cut but misses
gets to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to mid-off
pushed down the track back to the bowler
gets behind the line and defends with a dead bat
stays back, shuffles and works him to the on side
no turn this time, he stays back and punches it to point for a single
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it down to long-on
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
comes down the pitch, changes his mind and opts to defend forward, well bowled
turns it towards short fine leg and completes a sharp single
Hauritz drops it on a good length but it doesn't stop Shah from chipping down and lofting him over mid-off
steered to the covers for a single
reaches out and shapes to thrash it past cover but he finds the fielder
swivels at the crease and pulls along the ground
flighted outside off and pushed to the off side
stays beside the line and steers him to point
gives room and he steers him to the off side
quite stylish! Clarke drops it flatter and quicker, Prior picks it early, makes a bit of room and cuts hard past short third man
tries to nudge it fine but the ball clips his pads
floated on middle and leg and pushed to mid-off
sneaks past his pads down the leg side
gets forward early and defends
he's cutting well today, the ball skids through outside off and he cuts elegantly past short third man, Hussey does well at deep point to cut it off
comes forward and pushes it to the off side
hesitation! He pushes it towards mid-off and the batsmen set off, think again, then after a fumble go through with a single
lunges forward and pushes it towards mid-off
squeezes it to point for a single
fullish outside off and pushed towards mid-off
reaches out and chops it down to third man, the third fifty of the innings has been the quickest - off 56 balls
driven hard and fast down to deep extra cover and Ferguson has to hurry to slide and cut it off but he manages to pull it off
stays beside the line and cuts to point
strays on the pads and he clips him to fine leg
mistimes the on drive but he just manages to beat mid-on
driven hard down the pitch and picked up by the bowler
gets forward and drives to the deep on the off side and brings up the fifty stand
forced away hard through the off side but finds Watson at mid-off
turns it just wide of short fine leg for a single
drops it a bit short and he makes a bit of room and cuts to point
jams it on the blockhole but wide outside off, he squeezes it out to the off side
finds mid-off
drops it towards mid-off but decides against the single
high full toss at 91mph, too quick for him to seize on it and put it away, he steers it to backward point
strange looking shot, short down the leg side and he shapes to pull but instead spoons it towards fine leg
stays beside the line and steers it to point
stays behind the line and defends
cracker of a drive, he chips down the track to a half volley and biffs it hard down to long-off, the ball scorches through the outside and beats the fielder

gifts his wicket away, he comes down the pitch but Hauritz cleverly drops it short, the ball turns, grips and goes through the gate between bat and pad, Paine whips off the bails and Prior doesn't even bother to get back, didn't have to because he was a long way down
gets off the mark with a paddle down to fine leg, nice full toss to get first up
very slow through the air and defended with a dead bat
drops it short, makes room and cuts to point
clips it to deep square leg and the ball really gathers pace near the boundary, the fielder has to really hurry but he manages to cut it off, Ferguson fires the throw to the keeper
this one kicks up and creeps past the gap between bat and pad, not too far from the off stump either
angles it on the pads and he clips it down to deep square leg
gets a half stride forward and defends
wild swing and a miss, Siddle exerts himself a bit more and the ball kicks up outside off and thuds into the keeper's gloves
stays back and pushes it back to the bowler
slower ball on middle and off, he pushes it towards mid-off
steers him down to deep point and Ferguson is kept busy again
back of a length, he opens the face of the bat and steers him to third man
fires it on the blockhole and Shah squeezes it out to deep cover, slight fumble
drops it just a bit short and he swivels and pulls to deep square
chops him down to third man
hits a good length on middle and off, he defends back to the bowler
angles towards the leg side and he taps it to the on side
made it look so easy, Johnson gifts him a half volley down the leg side and Morgan whips it in the air and just clears deep square leg, seems like a short boundary down there
fires it wide down the leg side and Johnson can thank Paine for saving a certain boundary
much better, on the blockhole and he just manages to keep it out
keeps it on a good length and Morgan defends it back to the bowler
short and wide and he cuts to point
bowls it on the off stump line and he defends back to the bowler
another dot ball as Shah drives straight to mid-off
commits early to the front foot and he steers him down to cover
Watson comes round the wicket and looks up as Morgan sends the ball scurrying all the way to the vacant spaces at deep cover, too wide and spanked away
gets this one to come back in and he gets an inside edge down to fine leg
drops it with soft hands to the covers and sets off

tame again, the England batsmen don't seem to have a very long shelf life going by the evidence today, Johnson lands it outside off and gets it to straighten, Shah pokes at it and gets a thickish outside edge to Paine
gets a warm welcome from Johnson, takes his eyes off a short ball and it hits him flush on the helmet
and Mascarenhas endures another nervy moment as he gets a leading edge which falls short of cover, he also goes a long way back at the cease and nearly steps on his stumps
what's happening? Another short ball and Mascarenhas doesn't know whether to hook it or not, he gets a top edge which lands safe, the umpire penalises the bowler for height
beats him outside the off stump this time
once again he goes right across his stumps and nearly knocks them off with his back leg, he whips it away past midwicket
comes round the wicket, he pokes his bat out at it and the ball beats him

one for the album! Watson drops it on a good length from round the wicket and Morgan gets on top of the bounce, uses his bottom hand and pulls him over deep midwicket, clean hit and amazing follow through
pounded down the pitch but Watson does well to stop it and save a few runs
he mixes it up by bowling a slower ball but it lands on the half volley, Morgan scoops him high over mid-on
gently taps it to the off side and takes a single
he's on a roll here, he gets a friendly half volley on the pads and he picks his spot well by clipping him well wide of short fine leg
good length on the offstump, he opens the face of the bat and steers him to third man
clever change of pace from Johnson, somehow creeps past bat and pad, don't ask me how that didn't shave the off stump
checks his drive and squeezes it past the bowler, Johnson dives in vain
Powerplay revelry here, Johnson drops it short and Mascarenhas gets on his feet quickly, swivels and pulls over square leg

Dropped He was dropped 4 and half times by my estimate, Morgan gets forward and whips it high in the air across the line to deep square leg, Hussey runs forward, appears to have it in control, juggles it with it close to five times before dropping it on the turf
pulls this over midwicket for a couple
works it straight to short midwicket
goes for a wild slog and the ball takes a thick inside edge which just misses the off stump and rolls to fine leg
it's a low full toss outside off and he gets forward and crashes it past point
his eventful cameo comes to an end, Watson changes the pace and Mascarenhas doesn't pick the slower one, he mows him across the line but finds Johnson at short midwicket
slower ball and he pushes it past the bowler and down to long-on
stays back and punches it to the off side
full outside off and driven down to deep cover
cuts back in and he punches it back to the bowler, Bracken's keeping it tight
makes a bit of room and chops it past the gap between short third man and point, good team work by Hauritz and Siddle at third man
shuffles and works him towards fine leg and they push hard for the second run
stays back at the crease and works it across the line to deep midwicket
gets forward and pushes it wide of cover for a single
gets an inside edge to short midwicket
the slower ball really foxes him, he flays hard at the ball but it sneaks through bat and pad
cramps him for a bit of room and Broad mistimes the shot and fails to get it past the infield
width this time and he slashes it firmly to deep cover
there's a direct hit at the bowler's end but Broad times his dive well and makes his ground
slower ball, drops it a bit short outside off and he tries to steer it past short third man
stays back and chops him down to cover
excellent mopping up in the deep by Hussey, top class stuff, Broad times his cover drive well and really tests Hussey at deep cover but the fielder saves a run
chops it hard to point and Morgan doesn't bother about the single but Broad's a long way out, he makes a desperate attempts to get back
going, going and it's a heads-up to the crowd at the deep midwicket boundary! He picks the slower ball by getting on his knees and playing the cleanest of slog sweeps, brings up his fifty a well
swings too early and misses it completely
picks it from outside off and mows it down to long-on, in the air for a bit
leg cutter from Watson and Morgan tries to innovate by playing a reverse paddle, he ends up paddling it onto his body, strange shot
makes room, clears his back leg and crashes it past point for a boundary
makes room and really clubs a half volley down the ground to long-off
the future's bright, the future's Broad, Siddle drops it short and it's the perfect length for the tall Broad as he pulls past square leg
makes room and squeezes out a yorker past the bowler, good running too
nice delivery on the blockhole and Broad nearly slips at the crease as he works it down to mid-on
just holds the length back a bit and he scoops him down to long-off
fires a yorker length delivery and Siddle fields well off his own bowling
that's a direct hit,  Broad pushes it to mid-off and wants a single, Morgan hesitates but they go through with it and the direct hit by Ponting finds Broad short of his ground
he goes for the reverse paddle and gets a lot of elevation, clears short third man
he goes for another reverse paddle, but this time he gets a top edge and Siddle gets under it at point
slices it to point
slices it just wide of point
full outside off, he makes room and bashes it past point
I don;t think White saw that at all, it was well clear of him anyway, Bresnan makes room to a short delivery outside off and carves it over backward point, White was looking at the sun
full outside off and Bresnan makes room and scoops it straight to Bracken at extra cover
steers it wide of point for a single, can England get to 300?
full and swinging in on the leg stump, he makes room and squirts it to short third man
full and swinging in on the off stump, he quietly steers it down to the sweeper for a single
loosener down the leg side, Sidebottom tries to trickle it down to fine leg
shuffles and clips him down to deep square leg
classic shot, Rashid gets on his knees to a pitched up delivery outside off and slices it high in the air to deep point
not so elegant but he won't care, he makes room and gets a thick outside edge past the keeper's reach while aiming for the long-on boundary
makes room and thumps it in the air down to long-off, there's an overthrow and that allows another run
that's another street slog, he swings at a short delivery and the top edge clears the keeper and runs to fine leg
short down the leg side and he swings, wide called and they take an extra run
tries to cut a short delivery outside off but he misses, they attempt to steal a bye but Paine under-arms the ball onto the stumps with the batsman well short

inn2.comm: starts off with a half volley and he drives firmly to short cover
just holds the length back a bit and he defends with soft hands to the offside
risky but well clear of any fielder, he reaches out at a delivery wide outside off and he upper cuts it over the gap between the slips and gully
angled on the pads and he clips it to midwicket
lands outside off and holds its line before reaching the keeper
Paine gets his front pad forward and safely shoulders arms
angles it on the pads and he works it away past midwicket
stays back and defends to the off side, tells his partner to stay back
shuffles and works it off his hips down to square leg
keeps it on the angle close to the pads and he works it to square leg again
keeps it tight, cramps him for room, the batsman stays right behind and defends
fuller in length and he drives firmly but finds Bopara at short cover
terrific shot but not much appreciation from the crowd, he picks a length delivery early and clubs it high over midwicket, nearly carries all the way
gets beside the line and steers it to the off side
fuller in length honing in on the off stump, he just opens the face of the bat and squeezes it past backward point, the throw is wide and the back-up fielder fumbles too
clips it to the off side
short and wide outside off, he reaches out and mistimes the cut
full in length on the off stump and pushed through the line to mid-off
gets across and defends with a straight bat to the off side
gets across his stumps and defends to mid-on
keeps it tight, Watson stays behind the line and punches it to mid-on
gives him width and he cannot resist a slash, the thick outside edge flies past the slips and down to third man
really waits for it to come onto him before steering it to backward point
Paine tries to make room and whip it over the on side but the ball skids through and clips his pads
that's an excellent shot, banged in short and Paine reads the length early and clubs it down to fine leg
bowls it fuller and he pushes it back to the bowler
bowls a half volley on middle and leg, he offers the full face of the bat and drives crisply through the line and beats a diving mid-on, bit of a misfield
lands outside off, he goes for the drive but misses
full on the pads and worked away to fine leg
stays beside the line and he defends to the off side
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
good length on middle and leg, he flicks it to fine leg and a good throw from the deep restricts that to a single
cuts hard but finds point
lands on middle and leg, he turns the face of the bat and closes it to midwicket
he takes his eyes off a short delivery and the ball clips his shoulder, lobs up and just falls short of Strauss at slip
he strays down the leg side and Watson tries to work it through the on side but ends up flicking it to fine leg
he gives him width outside off, he reaches out and plays a square drive, the ball lobs up after the first bounce and clears backward point
good length on middle and leg, he defends back to the bowler
he shapes to cut but the ball skids through and beats the bat
stays beside the line and he angles it nicely wide of backward point
he picks the slower ball well, moves across his stumps, fetches it from outside off and clubs it over midwicket
stays behind the line and punches it hard back to the bowler
tempts him with width outside off and he pokes his bat out and misses
lands it on a good length on the off stump and he punches it back to the bowler
he immediately gives him the charge and flashes at a delivery slightly wide of the off stump, the outside edge rolls past the keeper
well bowled, gets it to come back in, Paine is solid in defense
similar delivery, he shows the full face of the bat and defends back to the bowler
gets behind the line and defends

soft dismissal in the end, we've seen quite a few today, Bresnan digs it in quite short and gets it to come in with the angle, Paine fails to control the pull and ends up getting a top edge lobs to Rashid at short fine leg
defended back to the bowler
gives him width and Watson shuffles across his crease and angles it wide of backward point
fullish in length outside off and pushed down to mid-off
punishes a half volley, he didn't hit it off the middle of the bat but the timing was still good enough to beat the bowler and mid-on who gave the chase
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
angles it away from the right-hander and he defends
angles it away from the right hander and he pushes it to the off side
intentional and very effective, Bresnan gives him width and Ponting opens the face of the bat and parries it past the massive gap between the keeper and gully
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side
short and pulled away, cries of 'catch it' but there's deep square-leg
gives him width outside off, he reaches out and steers him to third man
Sidebottom keeps it on the same line just around the off stump to Watson, he pushes it to the off side
good length on middle and leg, he stays behind the line and defends
punches it down to mid-off but he turns the face of the bat and mistimes it
on the stumps again, Ponting pushes it down the track

everyone run for cover! Shot of the match so far, Ponting chips down the track and elegantly lofts with the full face of the bat, that went into orbit, this was five times better than Denly's shot this afternoon
good length outside off and he steers it to third man
he swishes at a short delivery too early and fails to make contact, quicker one from Bresnan
that's a misfield, Ponting gets forward to a full delivery and drives off the full face of the bat, the fielder at mid-off ought to have had it covered
nearly gets a wicket off the first ball, the ball stops on him and he stops his shot, lobs and lands in front of cover
defends with more conviction this time
full on middle and leg, he defends back to the bowler
another false shot, this time over the on side, it stops on Ponting again but it just clears midwicket
good length on middle and leg, gets on the front foot and pushes it to mid-on
third false shot, he pulls too early and nearly gets an inside edge onto his stumps
opens the face and steers him down to third man
gets foreward and times the cover drive very well, the fielder is really tested at deep cover but he cuts it off
